To protect your privacy and security, we will take reasonable steps to verify your identity before granting access or making changes or modifications, this may include us needing to collect further information from you to confirm your identity. Unfortunately, we cannot always ensure that such changes or modifications will be reflected in all iterations of your information as previously stored.
We will respond to a verifiable consumer request within 30 days of its receipt.
CALIFORNIA PRIVACY RIGHTS AND DO NOT TRACK DISCLOSURES
In
some circumstances, California residents would have the right to request information from us regarding the manner in which we share your Personal Information with third parties for their direct marketing purposes. However, we do not share your Personal Information with third parties for the purpose of direct marketing. We do not honor Do Not Track requests. Under CCPA law you may only make a personal information request twice in a 12-month period, and we will need to collect information from you so that we can verify your identity to complete your information request.
